story:
&lt;p&gt;Hello and thankyou for taking the time to look at my page.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I&#39;m twelve years old and have battled through Anorexia, Depression and&amp;nbsp;OCD for the past year. And it was only after a disturbing and gut-wrenching wake up call in the form of a geography lesson that I fully began to realise the extent of poverty and its devastating effects, and I felt so guilty that I had so much food and water and was wasting it, when thousands and thousands of people world&amp;nbsp;wide are dying from starvation and lack of clean water through no choice of their own. So, I did some research and found that around&amp;nbsp;5000 children die every day from lack of clean water!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I have decided to make a change, to make a difference, to raise some much needed money to change the lives of those who need it. So please, dig deep and help me&amp;nbsp;to raise&amp;nbsp;some money. Donate only what you can afford... big or small - every little helps! A measly &amp;pound;5 could buy a bag of cement to build a hand dug latrine in places like Nigeria, and &amp;pound;60 could buy a hand dug rope pump to provide an entire&amp;nbsp;village with a lifelong supply of clean water!!&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Thanks again... Meghan xx&lt;/p&gt;
